Package RuleEngine.HierarchyProcessors

Class AttributeDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.ItemWithId
      • RuleEngine.AbstractDefinition
        • RuleEngine.HierarchyProcessors.AttributeDefinition
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConceptAttributeFunctionalDefinition, ConceptAttributeRelationalDefinition, DataAttributeFunctionalSingleDefinition, DataAttributeRelationalDefinition

    public abstract class AttributeDefinition
extends AbstractDefinition
    This is an abstract superclass for most of the AttributeProcessor-Definitions. It is used to store a number of common parameters for these classes.
    Except outputIndex, ll parameters come in pairs:
    - one can either specify the parameter explicitly in the definition, or
    - one can take the parameter from a certain position in the query array.
    See Also:
